abstract: A proposed anti-infiltration bill in Taiwan which the government says is needed to combat Chinese influence is spreading alarm amongst the Taiwanese business community in China, the Chinese government said on Wednesday.
snippet: A proposed anti-infiltration bill in Taiwan which the government says is needed to combat Chinese influence is spreading alarm amongst the Taiwanese business community in China, the Chinese government said on Wednesday.
lead_paragraph: BEIJING — A proposed anti-infiltration bill in Taiwan which the government says is needed to combat Chinese influence is spreading alarm amongst the Taiwanese business community in China, the Chinese government said on Wednesday.
headline_main: China Says Taiwan Anti-Infiltration Bill Causes 'Alarm' for Investors
headline_print_headline: China Says Taiwan Anti-Infiltration Bill Causes 'Alarm' for Investors

abstract: Foreign experts said they had quit advising a Hong Kong police watchdog on Wednesday due to doubts over its independence and ability to conduct an investigation into police conduct during months of anti-government protests.
snippet: Foreign experts said they had quit advising a Hong Kong police watchdog on Wednesday due to doubts over its independence and ability to conduct an investigation into police conduct during months of anti-government protests.
lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — Foreign experts said they had quit advising a Hong Kong police watchdog on Wednesday due to doubts over its independence and ability to conduct an investigation into police conduct during months of anti-government protests.
headline_main: Foreign Experts Quit Hong Kong Police Probe Questioning Its Independence
headline_print_headline: Foreign Experts Quit Hong Kong Police Probe Questioning Its Independence

abstract: Environmentalist Greens failed to win a seat in the Swiss federal government on Wednesday, unable to persuade parliament to oust a sitting minister and make room for an upstart party that made record gains in October elections.
snippet: Environmentalist Greens failed to win a seat in the Swiss federal government on Wednesday, unable to persuade parliament to oust a sitting minister and make room for an upstart party that made record gains in October elections.
lead_paragraph: ZURICH — Environmentalist Greens failed to win a seat in the Swiss federal government on Wednesday, unable to persuade parliament to oust a sitting minister and make room for an upstart party that made record gains in October elections.
headline_main: Swiss Greens Fall Short in Bid for First Cabinet Seat
headline_print_headline: Swiss Greens Fall Short in Bid for First Cabinet Seat

abstract: Britain’s election has been like the country’s late-autumn weather: chilly and dull, with blustery outbursts.

abstract: Thailand's Election Commission ruled Wednesday that a popular opposition party broke the law by accepting an illegal loan from its head, a decision that could lead to its dissolution and unsettle the country's politics.
snippet: Thailand's Election Commission ruled Wednesday that a popular opposition party broke the law by accepting an illegal loan from its head, a decision that could lead to its dissolution and unsettle the country's politics.
lead_paragraph: BANGKOK — Thailand's Election Commission ruled Wednesday that a popular opposition party broke the law by accepting an illegal loan from its head, a decision that could lead to its dissolution and unsettle the country's politics.
headline_main: Thai Election Body Rules Loan to Opposition Party Illegal
headline_print_headline: Thai Election Body Rules Loan to Opposition Party Illegal

abstract: France's prime minister said Wednesday that the full retirement age will be increased for the country's youngest, but offered concessions in an ill-fated effort to calm a nationwide protest against pension reforms that critics say will erode the nation's way of life.
snippet: France's prime minister said Wednesday that the full retirement age will be increased for the country's youngest, but offered concessions in an ill-fated effort to calm a nationwide protest against pension reforms that critics say will erode the n...
lead_paragraph: PARIS — France's prime minister said Wednesday that the full retirement age will be increased for the country's youngest, but offered concessions in an ill-fated effort to calm a nationwide protest against pension reforms that critics say will erode the nation's way of life.
headline_main: French Government Raises Retirement Age as Strikes Grind On
headline_print_headline: French Government Raises Retirement Age as Strikes Grind On

abstract: Cambodian Prime Minister Hun Sen on Wednesday dismissed a threat from the European Union (EU) to halt special trade privileges with the Southeast Asian country over human rights, saying Britain's exit from the bloc will ease the pain of sanctions.
snippet: Cambodian Prime Minister Hun Sen on Wednesday dismissed a threat from the European Union (EU) to halt special trade privileges with the Southeast Asian country over human rights, saying Britain's exit from the bloc will ease the pain of sanctions.
lead_paragraph: PHNOM PENH — Cambodian Prime Minister Hun Sen on Wednesday dismissed a threat from the European Union (EU) to halt special trade privileges with the Southeast Asian country over human rights, saying Britain's exit from the bloc will ease the pain of sanctions.
headline_main: Cambodia PM Dismisses EU Sanctions Threat, Says Brexit Will Limit Impact
headline_print_headline: Cambodia PM Dismisses EU Sanctions Threat, Says Brexit Will Limit Impact

abstract: Devastating bushfires that blanketed Australia's largest city with hazardous smoke this week have heightened public anger and raised political pressure on the government to do more to battle climate change.
snippet: Devastating bushfires that blanketed Australia's largest city with hazardous smoke this week have heightened public anger and raised political pressure on the government to do more to battle climate change.
lead_paragraph: SYDNEY — Devastating bushfires that blanketed Australia's largest city with hazardous smoke this week have heightened public anger and raised political pressure on the government to do more to battle climate change.
headline_main: Hazardous Sydney Smoke Turns Up Heat in Australia's Climate Politics
headline_print_headline: Hazardous Sydney Smoke Turns Up Heat in Australia's Climate Politics

abstract: A Pakistani court ordered on Wednesday that ailing former President Asif Ali Zardari be released on bail on medical grounds, so that he can seek medical treatment at a hospital of his choice in the country.
snippet: A Pakistani court ordered on Wednesday that ailing former President Asif Ali Zardari be released on bail on medical grounds, so that he can seek medical treatment at a hospital of his choice in the country.
lead_paragraph: ISLAMABAD — A Pakistani court ordered on Wednesday that ailing former President Asif Ali Zardari be released on bail on medical grounds, so that he can seek medical treatment at a hospital of his choice in the country.
headline_main: Pakistan Court Orders Release of Ailing Ex-President Zardari
headline_print_headline: Pakistan Court Orders Release of Ailing Ex-President Zardari

abstract: The nearly unanimous results in the Pacific islands chain exceeded expectations and could both accelerate independence and complicate relations across the region.
snippet: The nearly unanimous results in the Pacific islands chain exceeded expectations and could both accelerate independence and complicate relations across the region.
lead_paragraph: SYDNEY, Australia — The region of Bougainville, a collection of islands in the South Pacific, has voted overwhelmingly to become independent from Papua New Guinea, aiming to become the world’s newest nation.
